60.1	Fra_Angelico	Fra Angelico	Fra Angelico (c. 1395 â€“ February 18, 1455), born Guido di Pietro, was an Early Italian Renaissance painter described by Vasari in his Lives of the Artists as having "a rare and perfect talent". He was known to his contemporaries as Fra Giovanni da Fiesole (Brother John from Fiesole) and by Vasari as Fra Giovanni Angelico (Brother John the Angelic One).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Fra_Angelico_portrait.jpg/200px-Fra_Angelico_portrait.jpg
